      <section id="details">
        <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  ">Details</h2>


        
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>The European Union (EU) requires that an Attestation of Equivalence (AoE) is used to export hops and hops products to the EU from third countries.</p>

<p>In the United Kingdom (UK), the Rural Payments Agency (RPA) is expected to issue AoEs once RPA is registered with the EU as an authorised agency.</p>

<h2 id="enrol-with-rpa">Enrol with RPA</h2>
<p>Before applying for an AoE, you must first enrol with RPA.</p>

<p>To enrol, complete the AoE Enrolment form and return it to either the email or postal address shown on the form.</p>

<p>RPA will then:</p>

<ul>
  <li>record your authorised postal and email addresses</li>
  <li>check that an email address used to apply for an AoE is authorised</li>
</ul>

<p>If you want to update your details, you will need to submit another AoE Enrolment form.</p>

<h2 id="contact-rpa">Contact RPA</h2>
<p>If you have any queries, contact RPA.</p>

<p>Email</p>

<p>hops.exports@rpa.gov.uk</p>

<p>Helpline</p>

<p>03300 416 500</p>
</div>
</div>

      </section>
    </div>

